      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (normalized index of hemolysis, shear stress distribution) are directly relevant to the COU decision on worst-case hemolysis operating conditions.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and volume-averaged scalar shear stress are the primary QoIs. Both are directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1) and are the quantities used in the tolerance sensitivity study. Relevance is rated high."
